  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Securing Labbezanga-Kongo Kir&#xE9; Corridor through Improved Border Management and Cross Border Cooperation (BM-CBC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to enhance institutional and operational capacities to secure and stabilize the border between Mali and Niger. This will be achieved by developing stronger community engagement and more coherent approaches to border management in Gao (Mali) and Tillaberi (Niger) regions. This implies establishing mutual capacities to deal with border security threats, especially through the data collection and analysis capacities surrounding the MIDAS system, along the Labezzanga-Kongo Kir&#xE9; corridor and developing related cooperation mechanisms. First, it will improve authorities&#x2019; understanding of challenges and needs faced by border populations to foster mutual trust and maintain the social fabric to prevent the area from becoming a no man&#x2019;s land. This will be complemented by the extension of community prevention and communication networks operating in coordination with local and border authorities. Secondly, the proposed action will seek to build the capacities of border authorities, through the provision of modern and adapted equipment and improvement of border infrastructures in order to strengthen the State&#x2019;s presence, capacities and visibility on both sides of the border, and strengthen controls along the Labezzanga-Kongo Kir&#xE9; corridor, which is a strategic entry point for transnational criminal networks and Violent Extremism Organisations.</narrative>
  </description>
